definition.value: a renal pain AE that shows the pain in the kidney area identified by a percussion procedure.
a urine analysis result abnomal AE that shows cylindrical structures produced by the kidney and present in the urine.
a hepatitis AE that resutls in a hepatitis A viral infection.
a connective tissue disorder AE that shows an inflammation of the fascia, the connective tissue surrounding muscles, blood vessels, and nerves.
A tendon disorder AE that led to the formation of fibrous tissue in the tendon area
a fasciitis AE that shows an inflammation of the muscle fascia, the connective tissue surrounding muscles.
an eye disorder AE that causes visual disturbance and interfere with normal sight.
a cognitive disturbance AE that has mild cognitive disability; not interfering with work/school/life performance; specialized educational services/devices not indicated
a cognitive disturbance AE that has moderate cognitive disability; interfering with work/school/life performance but capable of independent living; specialized resources on part time basis indicated
a cognitive disturbance AE that has severe cognitive disability; significant impairment of work/school/life performance
an abortion AE that results in a retention of dead products of conception in utero for more than 8 weeks.
an edema AE that has an outcome of swelling in the eye.
Oral discomfort AE is a discomfort AE that shows an uncomfortable feeling in the oral.
a female reproductive system AE that has an outcome of the presence of a fluid-filled sac within a patient's ovary.
a female reproductive system AE that occurs in the placental area.
an inflammation AE that occurs at the central nervous system.
a nervous system AE that has outcome of lesion in the area of central nervous system.
a behavioral and neurological AE is characterized by motor coordination problems with daily activities.
a behavioral and neurological AE is a deficiency in the ability to write, primarily handwriting, but also coherence.
a sensory neuropathy AE than is the medical term for a sensation that exactly resembles that of small insects crawling on (or under) the skin.
a paresis AE that shows muscle weakness of the entire left or right side of the body.
an immunology and allergy investigation result abnormal AE that results in an increased level of an immunoglobulin.
a urinary system AE that shows abnormalities in the process of URINE voiding, including bladder control, frequency of URINATION, as well as the volume and composition of URINE.
a muscle twitch AE that has an outcome of contractions involuntary of muscle.
a nervous system AE that describes any neurologic deficit related to the spinal cord.
a optic neuritis AE that has outcome of optic neuritis in retrobulbar.

a eye AE that is an area of partial alteration in the field of vision consisting of a partially diminished or entirely degenerated visual acuity that is surrounded by a field of normal – or relatively well-preserved – vision.

A thyroiditis AE where the body interprets the thyroid glands and its hormone products T3, T4 and TSH as threats, therefore producing special antibodies that target the thyroid’s cells, thereby destroying it.
a colitis AE that is a disease that causes inflammation and sores (ulcers) in the lining of the large intestine.
an abnormal stool AE that shows pale or clay-colored stool.
a tumor AE that  is a group of blood cell tumors that develop from lymphatic cells.
a paresis AE that affects a single limb, usually an arm.
a eye AE that refers to weakness (-paresis) or paralysis (-plegia) of one or more extraocular muscles which are responsible for eye movements.
a eye AE that has outcome of slight differences in pupil size.
quadriplegia AE is paralysis caused by illness or injury that results in the partial or total loss of use of all four limbs and torso.
a CSF white blood cell count increased AE with more than the normal number of lymphocytes in cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).
a behavior and neurological AE that shows an decreased preformance
a skin AS that shows a mass at the skin.
an abnormal stool AE that shows an abnomal color in the feces.
an investigation result abnormal AE that shows an abnormal ultrasound scan result.
an injection site AE that shows some substance release from an injection site.
a tumor AE that has an outcome of the presense of a mass that arises from the axillary.
a behavioral and neurological AE that involves a slowing-down of thought and a reduction of physical movements in an individual.
an abscess AE that occurs at an injection-site. Note that an abscess is a collection of pus that has built up within a tissue of the body.
an ulcer AE that occurs at an injection-site.
a viral infection AE that is caused by a disseminated Bacillus Calmette-Guerin bacterial infection.
a paresis AE that shows a muscular weakness affecting all four extremities.
a menstrual disorder AE that shows an extremely light menstrual blood flow
a menstrual disorder AE that shows a menstrual period with abnormally heavy flow and falls under the larger category of abnormal uterine bleeding (AUB)
a male reproductive system AE in which spermatozoa in seminal fluid are dead or motionless
